President Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key Administration posts. Daniel B. Baer has been nominated as the United States Representative to the Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe. Michael G. Carroll has been nominated as the Inspector General for the United States Agency for International Development. James Cole, Jr. has been nominated as the General Counsel for the Department of Education. Keith M. Harper has been nominated as the United States Representative to the United Nations Human Rights Council. Catherine E. Lhamon has been nominated as the Assistant Secretary for Civil Rights in the Department of Education. Stephen W. Preston has been nominated as the General Counsel for the Department of Defense. President Obama has also announced his intent to appoint Brigadier General Anthony C. Funkhouser as the Commissioner of the Mississippi River Commission and Dr. Betsey Stevenson as a Member of the Council of Economic Advisers.